articles.title: Colombia : Successful containment of Covid-19?
articles.description:
Is Colombia an example of successful containment of the 2020 COVID-19 pandemic?  
 Colombia detected its first coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) case on March 2, 2020. From March 22 to April 25, it implemented a national lockdown that, apparently, allowed the country to keep a low incidence and mortality rate up to mid-May. Forced by the economic losses, the government then opened many commercial activities, which was followed by an increase in cases and deaths.

            Covid-19 : A deadly virus that shook the world
          
          
            
          
          
            
            Introduction and motivation
            Covid-19 has shaken the entire world. It has questioned the foundations of science, spirituality, humanity and all aspects of life on which we are currently surviving. It has taught us gratitude, acknowledgment, appreciation, love and care and most importantly how crucial health is.
            The world reaches a grim milestone as global deaths from COVID-19 surpass the 4 million mark. Compounded by fast moving variants and shocking inequity in vaccination, far too many countries in every region of the world are seeing sharp spikes in cases and hospitalization leading to an acute shortage of oxygen, treatments and driving a wave of death in parts of Africa, Asia and Latin America.
            The present analysis has been conducted to highlight the situation of the disease in the countries of Pakistan and Colombia in 2020 and the measures taken by various stakeholders coupled with support from the community to abate the risk of catastrophic spread of the virus.

articles.title: Is Pakistan a rockstar of Covid control strategy?
articles.description: Problem of a broken system is that we don’t have facts to win an argument. In recent weeks we have seen a lot of self-congratulatory announcements declaring Pakistan a winner of coronavirus control strategy. Many international magazines have also put Pakistan on the top of their lists. What is the real situation? If Pakistan’s Covid control strategy is so successful, then why are other countries not approaching them to learn from their experience? Why have top scientific journals not published their success story?

articles.description: Data and details about the situation of Covid-19 has been gathered from below websites.
articles.contents:
Data description
Data Sources
The data used for the study come from the following sources:
Source 1. OurWorldinData. All visualizations, data, and code produced by Our World in Data are completely open access under the Creative Commons BY license.
Source 2. SocioeconomicResponse. Data is collected by the UNCTs and reported through the UN INFO platform.CovidDashboard
Description
Confirmed cases and deaths: our data comes from the COVID-19 Data Repository by the Center for Systems Science and Engineering (CSSE) at Johns Hopkins University (JHU).
Hospitalizations and intensive care unit (ICU) admissions: our data comes from the European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC) for a select number of European countries; and government sources for the United Kingdom, the United States, Canada, Israel, Algeria, and Switzerland
Vaccinations against COVID-19: this data is collected by the Our World in Data team from official reports.
Other variables: this data is collected from a variety of sources (United Nations, World Bank, Global Burden of Disease, Blavatnik School of Government, etc.). More information is available in our codebook.
